for beginners

Overall pretty solid class. Most of the time the lecture is clear and the concept is well explained. However, I do have a few recommendations for the beginners who are considering taking this class. The lecture is conducted in a relatively fast-paced way, so please audit it first and only purchase this class if you can follow the quicky thinking pattern of this instructor. Examples and practice code are not embedded in the lecture videos which would add little hassles to your learning experience, and the dropbox hyperlink in the weekly reading session is somehow broken and hasn't been fixed till the point I am typing this review. And lastly, the weekly project/homework is actually pretty challenging for beginners, but a guarantee for an effective learning outcome!
